climbs.name: Ten B or Not Ten B

content.description: A thin fingercrack/seam that starts behind a pine tree. This thing is GRASSY, definitely could use some cleaning.
content.protection: fingers to micro cams, offset nuts might be useful.
content.location: On the left side of the right half of the Moya Wall. Behind a pine tree

climbs.name: Moya
climbs.fa: Sean Ward, Mary Stout, Mark McCall    June '95

content.description: Head up a set of wide double cracks. Funky movement
content.protection: Couple 1s, 2s, and 3s. A 4 might be useful
content.location: In the middle of the right half of the Moya Wall. Starts out of a patch of bushes that are the the right of two pine trees but to the left of the large juniper

content.description: Like a shorter, dirtier version of Hermaphrodite Flake. Tunnel up the large flake behind the juniper
content.location: In the large flake behind the large aesthetic juniper

content.description:
I don't think I'm the first to do this, if anyone has a name correction just let me know and I'll fix it!

Move up the corner, until you hit the roof. Get in good gear in the roof, then pull through on awesome gym holds. Grovel up the low angle, dirty finish for a few feet.
content.protection: Single rack to a #4. Small blue Metolious can be used right under the roof.
content.location: This route goes up the largeish left facing corner which is directly across the street from the eastern end of the western pullout.
